2/25/2010     Anna210    OMG--this is the most amazing reading! She totally 
blew me away and  thanks also to her guide David.  
 
12/19/2009     joanie56    Thank you for your accurate readings time after 
time, for all the  clarity and insight that you have given to me. I hope 
that who ever reads this  feadback will be incouraged to give you a call and 
find the answers to their  questions, as you always do it with truth, honesty 
and love. And I want to give  a thanks to David your spirit guide for his 
presence and answers too, thank him  for me again. Thank you SF.....best to 
you, love ya....Joanie   
 
1/4/2010     joanie56    Call Snowfire, she always gives me the insight 
that I need, and I  have the clarity on this new situation. I will be giving 
you a call soon. Thank  you again and tell David I said thank you 
sweetheart....LOL.Call Snowfire she  always steers me right!   
7/30/2010     keerie    Sf is by far the most accurate psychic on keen. I 
have not tried  them all but I have tried a good majority of the top 30 or so 
for the last 2  years . After I ran into sf after trying one psychic after 
the next , I've  stayed with her for over a year or so. I call at least 3-4 
times a month and  everything she says has been the truth and ended up what 
happened. She by far is  the real deal any other psychic you would be 
wasting your money   
 I  have really enjoyed these last few months in getting to know you, and 
all the  clarity and insight that you have provided for me, and I look 
forward to many  more readings and the conversations that we have with David. 
Thank you so much,  and you have a Heathy and Prosperous New Year! I will be in 
touch.....
 
9/10/2010     lilboss2u    Very interesting reading and somehow I feel she 
is going to be  correct about what she said. A definite "must call!!!!" 
Thanks Snowfire &  DAVID!! :-)  
 
10/3/2009     password55    OMG you are just so accurate. You said the 
exact words to me my son  said. You actually hear things. I am continually 
amazed by your gift.
